<li><a href="http://www.observer.com/2007/kurt-vonnegut-s-final-interview-s?dm_i=137097250" class="external text" title="http://www.observer.com/2007/kurt-vonnegut-s-final-interview-s?dm_i=137097250" rel="nofollow">Kurt Vonnegut’s Final Interview(s)</a> from the <a href="/wiki/New_York_Observer" title="New York Observer" class="mw-redirect">New York Observer</a> (July 10, July 15, 2007).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=crPrPpAaRXo" class="external text" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=crPrPpAaRXo" rel="nofollow">The Infinite Mind in Second Life with Kurt Vonnegut. August 2006</a> The Infinite Mind, made broadcast history as it aired a four-part special taped inside the 3-D virtual on-line community Second Life. Among those interviewed in front of a live, virtual audience was this 40-minute conversation with author Kurt Vonnegut.</li>
</ul>
